$interpreted: Sherlock: Hehe, as long as I can make it through today, it will be one full month...
Man: Mister, I want this one. How much is it?
Sherlock: I'm in a good mood today. You can have it for free.
Man: You serious!? Thank you so much~
Lisa: Can't we tell him about this tomorrow...
Ned: No good. If we have to scam Sir Sherlock to fulfill the ritual, we can't get him to wish us good luck from the bottom of his heart...
Sherlock: What's the matter? Why are you here?
Ned: Sir Sherlock, I have held on to Lisa's token for almost a month now. It should be enough proof that I really care about Lisa.
Ned: Therefore, I hope you can allow me to marry Lisa.

Sherlock: Hmph, I wonder if it's actually a full month?
You better not lie to me.
Sherlock: How could that be? I thought those three people took it from you and gave it to me!?
Ned: To tell Sir the truth... the Rainbow Roses in your possession are a counterfeit.
Sherlock: What? You bastard, how dare you cheat!
Lisa: Don't blame Ned. This was my idea!

Ned: Sir Sherlock, no matter how hard the trials you have given me, I've cleared them all. 
Please, trust me that I can give Lisa a happy life.
Ned: We would like your blessings for our marriage!

Sherlock: The time for the ritual is not up yet!
Since you dared to bring the real flower here,
Sherlock: I'll take them back myself!
Ned: Are you alright, Sir Sherlock?

Ned: I successfully protected the token. 
Does this mean I've cleared your trial?
Lisa: Stop being nice to him! He had it coming all this time! Let's go~
Lisa: Darling, what's the matter?

Ned: Lisa, I still feel bad about this...
If we have the opportunity, shouldn't we still apologize to Sir Sherlock?
Lisa: NO! He is the one who started this by using dirty tricks himself. Why should I be the one who apologizes first!
Ned: Sir Sherlock only did those things because he cared about you, perhaps a bit too much.

Ned: I was an orphan as far as I can remember. 
Thus, when I see Sir Sherlock worrying so much about you, it makes me a little envious.
Ned: I feel like having family who truly cares about you is an amazing and blessed thing.
Ned: If the bond between family members is destroyed by something as minor as this, that is too unfortunate, don't you think?
Lisa: O, ok... I get it...
